subject: LogEntry: Link Chassis log to Drive and Processor
commitMessage:
LogEntry: Link Chassis log to Drive and Processor

The log entries are link to device/resoruces related the chassis that
created the log service.

The logs are linked to the Status where is has a list of Condition to
help indicate the resource status. Each Condition is linked to
a LogEntry URI.

Each LogEntry will contain Message and Severity like in Condition. The
LogEntry is used instead, because it allow us to use the
`xyz.openbmc_project.Logging.Entry` to create the log on the bmc side.
There are no existing support for Condition.Message in OpenBMC.

Tested:
Passed Redfish Validator
```
*** /redfish/v1/Systems/system/Storage/board_0/Drives/board_0
Limiting namespace has no version, erasing: Resource
         Type (#Drive.v1_7_0.Drive), GET SUCCESS (time: 0.084656)
         PASS
```

```
{
  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Systems/system/Storage/board_0/Drives/board_0",
  "@odata.type": "#Drive.v1_7_0.Drive",
  "Id": "board_0",
  "Links": {
    "Chassis": {
      "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Chassis/board_0"
    }
  },
  "Name": "Board",
  "Status": {
    "Conditions": [
      {
        "LogEntry": {
          "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Chassis/board_0/LogServices/DeviceLog/Entries/log0"
        },
        "MessageId": "Drive.0.0.log0"
      }
    ],
    "Conditions@odata.count": 1,
    "Health": "OK",
    "HealthRollup": "OK",
    "State": "Enabled"
  }
}
```

Signed-off-by: Willy Tu <wltu@google.com>
